        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 3:21PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Farisita, or 46 miles east of Alamosa, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Farisita, Greenhorn Mountain, and Spring Burn Scar north of Highway
160.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
